                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14413103" author="bentmann" created="Wed, 11 Jun 2008 13:36:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Proposed patch which simply retains a leading double slash. As the unit test shows, this makes UNC paths as constructed by Java (btw, these have only 4 successive slashes on a Sun JRE 1.6.0_04, not 5 as used by the reporter) successfully pass &lt;tt&gt;DefaultModelInheritanceAssembler.appendPath()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14413150" author="jdcasey" created="Thu, 3 Jul 2008 19:06:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushing to 2.0.11 so we can have a smaller set of high-value issues to target for the next release (2.0.10).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14414256" author="pnyheim" created="Mon, 26 Jan 2009 07:13:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I would just like to add an observation to this issue.&lt;br/&gt;
In our setup, we have extracted the url to a property in the pom&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-xml&quot;&gt; 
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;properties&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;distMgtSiteUrl&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;file:////my.server.com/share&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/distMgtSiteUrl&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-tag&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/properties&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt; and in that case, no path manipulation is done in &lt;tt&gt;DefaultModelInheritanceAssembler.appendPath()&lt;/tt&gt;. as the path passed to it will be the non-interpolated property: &lt;tt&gt;${distMgtSiteUrl&lt;/tt&gt;}.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17998324" author="JIRAUSER302100" created="Sat, 5 Jul 2025 14:10:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven/issues/5038&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven#5038&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
